    BDD
    Binary Decision Diagrams (BDDs) are used for efficient computation of many common problems.
    BDD.AllSatIterator
    Iterator that returns all satisfying assignments as byte arrays.
    BDD.BDDIterator
    BDDIterator is used to iterate through the satisfying assignments of a BDD.
    BDD.BDDToString
    BDDToString is used to specify the printing behavior of BDDs with domains.
    BDD.GCPrehook
    Functional interface for GC prehook callbacks.
    BDDACLWrapper
    Computes BDD for ACL rules and Forwardding rules Note: The true, false, bdd variables, the negation of bdd variables: their reference count are already set to maximal, so they will never be garbage collected.
